"INTRO_PARAGRAPH2" = "Sleep apnea can make it difficult to get a full night of rest, which can lead to tiredness during the day. The condition can also increase the risk for high blood pressure, heart attack, stroke, and type 2 diabetes. Early diagnosis and treatment of sleep apnea may reduce the risk for physical and mental health conditions.";
"ARTICLE_DESCRIPTION" = "How breathing disturbances can impact your sleep.";
"ARTICLE_TITLE" = "What Is Sleep Apnea?";
"SECTION2_HEADER" = "How do you know if you have sleep apnea?";
"SECTION3_PARAGRAPH1" = "It is important to bring any concerns about your sleep to your doctor or care team. Your care team will review your medical history and do a physical exam. Depending on the results, they may have you do a sleep test. A sleep test allows your care team to see what is causing your sleep disturbances. This test can be done at a sleep lab or at home using a portable monitor.";
"SECTION1_PARAGRAPH1" = "The most common type of sleep apnea is known as obstructive sleep apnea. It occurs when the muscles located in the back of your throat relax, which can cause your airway to narrow or close as you breathe. Other forms of sleep apnea such as central sleep apnea can occur but are less common. If you have any concerns about sleep apnea, you should mention them to your doctor or care team.";
"SECTION2_PARAGRAPH1" = "Often people with sleep apnea do not realize they have symptoms because they occur during sleep. If you sleep next to someone, they may notice loud snoring, gasping for air, or pauses in your breathing.";
"SECTION2_PARAGRAPH2" = "During the day, you can look for signs of sleep apnea such as excessive daytime sleepiness, difficulty paying attention, morning headaches, and irritability.";
"SECTION1_HEADER" = "What happens with sleep apnea?";
"SECTION3_PARAGRAPH2" = "There are many different ways sleep apnea can be treated. Your doctor will review which treatment may work best for you. One common way to treat sleep apnea is using a device called a continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP) machine. This machine uses air pressure to help keep your airway open at night so you can sleep easier.";
"INTRO_PARAGRAPH1" = "The vast majority of people have regular, rhythmic breathing patterns while they sleep, but it is also fairly common for people to experience short, temporary interruptions to their breathing. Sleep apnea is a common condition where someone has interruptions in their breathing night after night. In any given sleep session, you could experience anywhere from just a few disturbances to more than 30 per hour.";
